1
00:00:56,151 --> 00:00:57,152
[Previously on]

2
00:00:57,152 --> 00:01:00,139
<i>Jae Seong said he swerved
for a cat and hit the rail.</i>

3
00:01:00,139 --> 00:01:02,424
<i>Soccer is off the table.</i>

4
00:01:02,424 --> 00:01:04,226
<i>- Good morning, Chairman.
- Good morning, Chairman.</i>

5
00:01:04,226 --> 00:01:07,028
<i>Because of you, my soccer career is over.</i>

6
00:01:07,028 --> 00:01:08,396
<i>So how much do you want?</i>

7
00:01:08,396 --> 00:01:11,105
<i>Want ten billion? Write ten billion.</i>

8
00:01:11,105 --> 00:01:13,068
<i>Jae Seong was driving.</i>

9
00:01:13,068 --> 00:01:16,239
<i>Jae Gyeong's the one who whispered to run.</i>

10
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:18,373
<i>Forget about the Chairman's chair.</i>

11
00:01:18,373 --> 00:01:20,165
<i>I'll announce it at the board.</i>

12
00:01:20,165 --> 00:01:22,110
<i>- Stop!
- Stop!</i>

13
00:01:24,772 --> 00:01:26,914
<i>Why's it so loud?</i>

14
00:01:28,372 --> 00:01:30,872
<i>Of all people, why am I that kid?</i>

15
00:01:30,872 --> 00:01:34,956
<i>If I get close, do we both die?</i>

16
00:01:34,956 --> 00:01:37,569
<i>This is our only way out.</i>

17
00:01:37,569 --> 00:01:39,670
<i>Nothing ever sticks to him.</i>

18
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:42,069
<i>Now we can force him out legally.</i>

19
00:01:42,069 --> 00:01:45,109
<i>I will make it up to you properly.</i>

20
00:01:45,109 --> 00:01:47,929
<i>I'm Hwang Jun Hyeon, Choiseong Group intern.</i>

21
00:01:47,929 --> 00:01:50,173
<i>Don't tell anyone I'm his daughter.</i>

22
00:01:50,173 --> 00:01:51,873
<i>And don't say my real name.</i>

23
00:01:51,873 --> 00:01:54,309
<i>Don't act close to me, Kang Bang Geul.</i>

24
00:01:54,309 --> 00:01:58,049
<i>He briefly regained consciousness
and left this letter.</i>

25
00:01:58,049 --> 00:02:02,639
<i>Every Choiseong employee has
the right to become chairman.</i>

26
00:02:02,639 --> 00:02:05,440
<i>Then do I qualify too?</i>

27
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:07,255
<i>To become chairman of Choiseong?</i>

28
00:02:07,255 --> 00:02:09,291
<i>This is only the beginning.</i>

29
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:12,627
<i>Everything you enjoyed thanks to me,</i>

30
00:02:12,627 --> 00:02:15,363
<i>I'll take it back one by one.</i>

31
00:02:15,363 --> 00:02:17,398
<i>Look forward to it.</i>

32
00:02:25,239 --> 00:02:27,918
That's him? The one the Chairman ran over?

33
00:02:27,918 --> 00:02:29,878
Has he lost his mind?

34
00:02:29,878 --> 00:02:31,579
Does he know where he is, talking like that?

35
00:02:31,579 --> 00:02:33,281
Discipline here is a joke.

36
00:02:33,281 --> 00:02:37,006
Now some intern's running wild. Unbelievable.

37
00:02:37,006 --> 00:02:40,055
Smooth operation.

38
00:02:40,055 --> 00:02:42,390
What did he do this time?

39
00:02:50,498 --> 00:02:52,700
It's really you, Kang Bang Geul.

40
00:02:55,939 --> 00:02:58,740
It's been a while, Sis.

41
00:03:00,742 --> 00:03:02,502
I cut you some slack for being the victim...

42
00:03:02,502 --> 00:03:06,581
and you crash the meeting talking nonsense?

43
00:03:06,581 --> 00:03:08,183
I can't remember.

44
00:03:08,183 --> 00:03:10,772
I finished the presentation
and went back to Materials,

45
00:03:10,772 --> 00:03:12,821
and woke up here. I swear.

46
00:03:12,821 --> 00:03:15,223
Feels like an aftereffect from the accident.

47
00:03:15,223 --> 00:03:17,593
What did I even say?

48
00:03:17,593 --> 00:03:19,828
You don't remember the presentation?

49
00:03:19,828 --> 00:03:24,666
My team was stuck on inventory,
so I took a look.

50
00:03:24,666 --> 00:03:27,736
Yujin Networks, IB Global, Hwain Dynamics,

51
00:03:27,736 --> 00:03:31,672
three firms, clean books for years,
no stock left over,

52
00:03:31,672 --> 00:03:33,341
oddly enough.

53
00:03:34,242 --> 00:03:36,378
Some aren't even manufacturers.

54
00:03:36,378 --> 00:03:38,939
Some just sell for the Trading affiliates,

55
00:03:38,939 --> 00:03:41,683
but the numbers are staggering.

56
00:03:41,683 --> 00:03:43,651
So I thought,

57
00:03:44,572 --> 00:03:46,521
these companies...

58
00:03:47,372 --> 00:03:49,424
These companies what?

59
00:03:54,368 --> 00:03:55,906
Cut the freeloaders out,

60
00:03:55,906 --> 00:03:57,532
deal with Trading direct,

61
00:03:57,532 --> 00:04:01,036
and we'd save tens of billions, that's all.

62
00:04:01,036 --> 00:04:02,470
That's really all?

63
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:05,474
Nothing else you know?

64
00:04:05,474 --> 00:04:08,028
Should I know more?

65
00:04:08,994 --> 00:04:10,011
Who said you should?

66
00:04:10,011 --> 00:04:11,170
Look, because of me,

67
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:13,069
the hit-and-run got smoothed over,

68
00:04:13,069 --> 00:04:14,749
so you owe me, all the way.

69
00:04:14,749 --> 00:04:16,500
We're practically family.

70
00:04:17,986 --> 00:04:20,889
So that means I get a permanent spot, right?

71
00:04:20,889 --> 00:04:22,490
If you fire me now...

72
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:25,789
You're exactly like your dad who ran away.

73
00:04:25,789 --> 00:04:28,229
Who do you think you are?

74
00:04:28,229 --> 00:04:31,065
Are you picking a fight with the president?

75
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:35,668
<i>I came for the 300 billion you stole.</i>

76
00:04:35,668 --> 00:04:37,839
<i>I'm taking it back myself.</i>

77
00:04:41,476 --> 00:04:44,146
No leaks from Sales, I checked.

78
00:04:44,146 --> 00:04:46,614
I also told the CEOs of Yujin, IB, and Hwain...

79
00:04:46,614 --> 00:04:48,183
To keep their mouths shut.

80
00:04:48,183 --> 00:04:51,953
The rookie was just spouting nonsense.

81
00:04:52,821 --> 00:04:54,255
It still bothers me.

82
00:04:54,255 --> 00:04:57,617
What if we freeze their accounts for now?

83
00:04:57,617 --> 00:05:00,595
Freezing them right before closing...

84
00:05:00,595 --> 00:05:02,297
Will only draw more attention.

85
00:05:02,297 --> 00:05:05,979
Stop making excuses and find a way.

86
00:05:05,979 --> 00:05:08,103
I'll talk to Sales.

87
00:05:08,103 --> 00:05:10,839
I'll tell them to hide
the ledgers from Support...

88
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:12,517
And buy us some time.

89
00:05:12,517 --> 00:05:14,876
Keep it quiet.

90
00:05:14,876 --> 00:05:15,911
Seriously!

91
00:05:15,911 --> 00:05:17,478
- Yes.
- Yes, sir.

92
00:05:19,173 --> 00:05:21,716
President Kang Jae Gyeong is looking for you.

93
00:05:23,418 --> 00:05:25,427
Said it's a family matter.

94
00:05:28,072 --> 00:05:30,377
[Application]
You really pulled it off, Bang Geul.

95
00:05:30,377 --> 00:05:33,661
Are Trading's standards that low?

96
00:05:33,661 --> 00:05:36,467
I don't want to talk to you.
Get out of my company.

97
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:37,469
Brother.

98
00:05:37,469 --> 00:05:38,733
Don't call me brother.

99
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:40,539
Don't you call me brother.

100
00:05:40,539 --> 00:05:43,037
I'm already in a bad mood, so don't push it.

101
00:05:43,037 --> 00:05:44,568
Why?

102
00:05:44,568 --> 00:05:47,775
She really threw herself into the grunt work.

103
00:05:47,775 --> 00:05:50,679
They loved her copying skills.

104
00:05:50,679 --> 00:05:52,947
I hear you make great coffee.

105
00:05:54,087 --> 00:05:56,472
I should've let her make mine.

106
00:05:56,472 --> 00:05:58,753
My espresso with warm milk is the best.

107
00:05:58,753 --> 00:06:00,388
Want me to make you some?

108
00:06:01,556 --> 00:06:02,590
Is this funny?

109
00:06:02,590 --> 00:06:04,306
Having the time of your life?

110
00:06:04,306 --> 00:06:07,346
Can't I just work here?

111
00:06:07,346 --> 00:06:09,631
I'm sick of playing around in the States.

112
00:06:09,631 --> 00:06:10,965
You get to save money, too.

113
00:06:10,965 --> 00:06:12,939
No need to pay my friends to spy on me.

114
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:15,407
You can see for yourself how dumb I am.

115
00:06:15,407 --> 00:06:17,572
Nice speech. Guess you aced the interview.

116
00:06:17,572 --> 00:06:19,107
Take her if you like her.

117
00:06:19,107 --> 00:06:21,347
You know me. I'm not smart.

118
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:23,067
I have zero corporate ambition.

119
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,907
I just wanted Mom's cooking.

120
00:06:24,907 --> 00:06:26,714
Sick of burgers and pasta.

121
00:06:26,714 --> 00:06:27,916
Please.

122
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:29,383
I'm begging you.

123
00:06:30,817 --> 00:06:33,216
Prove it.

124
00:06:33,216 --> 00:06:35,623
That you have no ambition.

125
00:06:35,623 --> 00:06:37,825
Give me the land in Gangwon Dad gave you.

126
00:06:37,825 --> 00:06:39,728
And the Gangnam building.

127
00:06:43,072 --> 00:06:44,699
No?

128
00:06:45,705 --> 00:06:48,173
No, I'm fine with it.

129
00:06:48,173 --> 00:06:50,705
I've been smiling this whole time.

130
00:06:50,705 --> 00:06:51,944
They're yours.

131
00:06:51,944 --> 00:06:54,542
I don't need any real estate.

132
00:06:54,542 --> 00:06:57,212
If I give it up, can I stay?

133
00:06:57,212 --> 00:06:59,614
Can I move back home?

134
00:07:00,922 --> 00:07:03,685
Keep quiet so no one talks.

135
00:07:03,685 --> 00:07:05,587
Make sure no one knows you're his daughter.

136
00:07:05,587 --> 00:07:07,589
Of course.

137
00:07:07,589 --> 00:07:09,624
I won't even say your names.

138
00:07:09,624 --> 00:07:11,859
I'll live quietly as Casey Kang.

139
00:07:11,859 --> 00:07:14,395
Should I sign a waiver and use my thumbprint?

140
00:07:14,395 --> 00:07:16,464
I'll use all ten fingers.

141
00:07:31,728 --> 00:07:34,716
You're ruthless, Kang Jae Gyeong.

142
00:07:34,716 --> 00:07:36,472
Holding onto ninety-nine rooms,

143
00:07:36,472 --> 00:07:38,720
[Deed of Assignment and Waiver of Rights]
you couldn't just spare her a single one?

144
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,022
Did you really have to shake down
a kid for her allowance?

145
00:07:41,022 --> 00:07:45,426
You liked her mom best out of all the staff.

146
00:07:45,426 --> 00:07:48,605
Right after Mom died, as if she was waiting...

147
00:07:48,605 --> 00:07:52,206
She took over the master bedroom
in under a year.

148
00:07:52,206 --> 00:07:55,572
She was sleeping with Dad long before that.

149
00:07:55,572 --> 00:07:57,472
Everything of Mom's...

150
00:07:57,472 --> 00:07:59,707
I'll make sure she gets none of it.

151
00:07:59,707 --> 00:08:03,044
I'll throw her out with absolutely nothing.

152
00:08:03,044 --> 00:08:04,815
After betraying her master
to live the high life...

153
00:08:04,815 --> 00:08:06,847
That's how a servant should end up, right?

154
00:08:08,338 --> 00:08:11,386
A servant's end?

155
00:08:11,386 --> 00:08:14,188
Sounds entertaining.

156
00:08:15,106 --> 00:08:17,254
You help, too.

157
00:08:17,254 --> 00:08:19,460
If you're loyal to Mom.

158
00:08:24,505 --> 00:08:28,139
Hey Mom, what are you up to?

159
00:08:28,139 --> 00:08:29,904
Did you eat?

160
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,939
No.

161
00:08:31,939 --> 00:08:33,872
I have good news.

162
00:08:33,872 --> 00:08:35,291
They said I can work.

163
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:38,046
And I can move back in.

164
00:08:38,046 --> 00:08:39,095
<i>Really?</i>

165
00:08:39,095 --> 00:08:41,082
They allowed it?

166
00:08:41,082 --> 00:08:42,267
Honey?

167
00:08:43,751 --> 00:08:45,283
So stop worrying.

168
00:08:45,283 --> 00:08:47,388
Your daughter is a full-time employee now.

169
00:08:47,388 --> 00:08:49,561
<i>How generous of them.</i>

170
00:08:49,561 --> 00:08:51,859
They're not bad at heart.

171
00:08:51,859 --> 00:08:55,139
<i>Still, mind your manners at all times.</i>

172
00:08:55,139 --> 00:08:57,432
<i>Don't ever be a burden on them.</i>

173
00:08:57,432 --> 00:08:59,100
<i>Okay? Bang Geul.</i>

174
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,202
Are you even listening to me?

175
00:09:03,705 --> 00:09:04,864
<i>I'd better head back inside.</i>

176
00:09:04,864 --> 00:09:06,273
Okay.

177
00:09:11,931 --> 00:09:13,372
You scared me half to death!

178
00:09:13,372 --> 00:09:16,591
They'd never give freely,
so what did they take now?

179
00:09:16,591 --> 00:09:17,885
What kind of idiot do you take me for?

180
00:09:17,885 --> 00:09:19,293
They swore shares were off the table.

181
00:09:19,293 --> 00:09:21,652
The same crew screaming
to fob you off with land.

182
00:09:21,652 --> 00:09:23,892
What'd you hand over, huh?

183
00:09:23,892 --> 00:09:27,461
What's it to you whatever I sign away?

184
00:09:28,706 --> 00:09:30,572
She got robbed, she really did.

185
00:09:30,572 --> 00:09:32,433
That hopeless girl.

186
00:09:35,261 --> 00:09:38,261
<i>Then who said you could do that to my dad?</i>

187
00:09:38,261 --> 00:09:39,574
<i>You ruined my plan.</i>

188
00:09:39,574 --> 00:09:42,043
<i>Don't tell anyone I'm his daughter.</i>

189
00:09:42,043 --> 00:09:44,680
<i>And don't say my real name.</i>

190
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,647
Kang Bang Geul.

191
00:09:47,482 --> 00:09:50,652
Why'd you join Choiseong?

192
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:55,305
Oh, right.

193
00:09:55,305 --> 00:09:58,259
Heard Director Song drew up
the Yuncheon port plan too.

194
00:09:58,259 --> 00:09:59,927
The guy's seriously got the goods.

195
00:09:59,927 --> 00:10:01,596
That's the golden track right there.

196
00:10:01,596 --> 00:10:02,895
As for VP Choi.

197
00:10:02,895 --> 00:10:05,333
At this rate, won't President Jae Seong
land the chair?

198
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:07,135
[Yuncheon Port Plan, Director Song's work]
So what about President Jae Gyeong?

199
00:10:07,135 --> 00:10:09,595
Is she just sitting idle?

200
00:10:09,595 --> 00:10:12,472
Word is she's buying out
a solid-state battery firm.

201
00:10:12,472 --> 00:10:13,939
[Chemicals, Solid-State Battery]
If that one hits big?

202
00:10:13,939 --> 00:10:16,210
["Chemicals is Choiseong's core"]
Then Chemicals wins.

203
00:10:24,637 --> 00:10:25,953
Hello.

204
00:10:25,953 --> 00:10:27,657
Hello.

205
00:10:27,657 --> 00:10:29,624
That one and that one.

206
00:10:29,624 --> 00:10:31,259
Actually, just box up
all the tasty stuff for me.

207
00:10:31,259 --> 00:10:33,888
Coming right up.

208
00:10:37,698 --> 00:10:40,101
- Looks delicious.
- What's this?

209
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:42,536
Thanks for the treat.

210
00:10:44,672 --> 00:10:46,472
What's all this?

211
00:10:46,472 --> 00:10:47,979
- Why's this so good?
- It's delicious.

212
00:10:47,979 --> 00:10:50,705
- Pretty amazing, right?
- Yeah.

213
00:10:50,705 --> 00:10:53,147
Eat up, have this one too.

214
00:10:53,147 --> 00:10:54,705
You bought a whole haul.

215
00:10:54,705 --> 00:10:56,684
Generous, aren't you?

216
00:10:56,684 --> 00:10:59,187
Your cleaning zones
got switched this time, right?

217
00:10:59,187 --> 00:11:02,623
I moved over
to the Chemicals president's office.

218
00:11:02,623 --> 00:11:05,092
They say President Jae Gyeong is a tough one.

219
00:11:05,092 --> 00:11:07,128
- So that means you're with the?
- I'm worried sick.

220
00:11:07,128 --> 00:11:08,872
Word is President Jae Seong is nasty.

221
00:11:08,872 --> 00:11:11,512
That brother and sister, a matched set.

222
00:11:12,781 --> 00:11:15,303
Eat up and get your strength back!

223
00:11:15,303 --> 00:11:17,139
- Stay strong!
- Stay strong!

224
00:11:18,338 --> 00:11:20,474
Mind if I take this one to go?

225
00:11:26,672 --> 00:11:29,917
[Janitor Lounge]
Piecing this together will take me all night.

226
00:11:35,206 --> 00:11:36,639
Thanks for all your hard work.

227
00:11:36,639 --> 00:11:37,726
You startled me.

228
00:11:37,726 --> 00:11:39,605
Have some while you work.

229
00:11:39,605 --> 00:11:41,907
Oh, you shouldn't have.

230
00:11:41,907 --> 00:11:42,868
Worn out, aren't you?

231
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:47,368
President Jae Seong must travel a lot
for that port deal.

232
00:11:47,368 --> 00:11:49,270
A run to Yuncheon's nothing, really.

233
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:52,940
Speaking of which,
they say it's decided this month?

234
00:11:53,772 --> 00:11:55,505
That's great news.

235
00:11:55,505 --> 00:11:58,079
Easier on you too, no more long hauls.

236
00:11:58,079 --> 00:11:59,613
That's right.

237
00:12:01,705 --> 00:12:02,806
Let me carry that for you.

238
00:12:02,806 --> 00:12:03,839
All right.

239
00:12:03,839 --> 00:12:05,106
I'll wrap this up fast.

240
00:12:05,106 --> 00:12:08,330
Yes, I'll wait right here for you.

241
00:12:14,338 --> 00:12:16,130
Not half bad.

242
00:12:17,164 --> 00:12:19,668
Maybe I'll grab a car while I'm at it.

243
00:12:21,536 --> 00:12:23,534
No cash, though.

244
00:12:59,872 --> 00:13:01,842
How'd you crack the chairman's office code?

245
00:13:01,842 --> 00:13:02,977
Hey, hold on a second.

246
00:13:02,977 --> 00:13:04,045
Here to steal something?

247
00:13:04,045 --> 00:13:06,012
Think I didn't notice you tailing me?

248
00:13:06,012 --> 00:13:09,550
Jae Gyeong or Jae Seong, whose spy are you?

249
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:11,519
Should I call security?

250
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:12,592
Or maybe the police?

251
00:13:12,592 --> 00:13:13,931
That hurts.

252
00:13:13,931 --> 00:13:15,190
I said it hurts.

253
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:17,491
I'll tell you every last thing
you're dying to know.

254
00:13:17,491 --> 00:13:19,159
Just let go first!

255
00:13:24,705 --> 00:13:26,968
You've got some nerve.

256
00:13:26,968 --> 00:13:28,035
Hey.

257
00:13:28,035 --> 00:13:29,410
Your father's the one who told me to use it.

258
00:13:29,410 --> 00:13:32,640
He gave me the office code and the safe spot,
all of it.

259
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,783
How else would I know, think about it.

260
00:13:34,783 --> 00:13:36,711
You should be down on your knees begging.

261
00:13:36,711 --> 00:13:38,343
And you drag my dad into this?

262
00:13:38,343 --> 00:13:41,273
You enjoy leeching off
the presidents that much?

263
00:13:41,273 --> 00:13:44,318
The ones who shattered my leg
and killed my career.

264
00:13:44,318 --> 00:13:45,786
It was your sister and brother.

265
00:13:45,786 --> 00:13:47,597
Not Chairman Kang at all.

266
00:13:47,597 --> 00:13:50,024
- What?
- Chairman Kang Yong Ho asked this of me.

267
00:13:50,024 --> 00:13:52,793
Expose the real culprits and protect Choiseong.

268
00:13:52,793 --> 00:13:55,897
You're the one who framed my dad
for that hit and run.

269
00:13:55,897 --> 00:13:58,133
Go to the station and say it yourself.

270
00:13:58,133 --> 00:13:59,800
Then I'll believe you.

271
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:01,220
I can't go!

272
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:02,269
There's no proof.

273
00:14:02,269 --> 00:14:03,806
With nothing to pin it on the twins,

274
00:14:03,806 --> 00:14:05,072
who's going to take my word for it?

275
00:14:05,072 --> 00:14:06,907
If there's no proof, then go dig it up!

276
00:14:06,907 --> 00:14:09,617
If no one believes you, make them believe!

277
00:14:15,139 --> 00:14:17,151
Now it all makes sense.

278
00:14:17,151 --> 00:14:20,903
Why you grabbed my collar
raging over your dad laid up.

279
00:14:20,903 --> 00:14:23,657
You want to land one solid blow on the twins.

280
00:14:24,492 --> 00:14:27,761
Or is it your bedridden dad
you want to prove something to?

281
00:14:28,896 --> 00:14:30,831
Why you came back here.

282
00:14:30,831 --> 00:14:33,301
Just how far your abilities really stretch.

283
00:14:34,068 --> 00:14:36,572
Chasing every team dinner,
taking on all the grunt work.

284
00:14:36,572 --> 00:14:39,740
You're dying to prove your father was wrong.

285
00:14:41,109 --> 00:14:43,911
That you're a better person than your siblings.

286
00:14:43,911 --> 00:14:45,685
- That's what you're out to show.
- Shut it.

287
00:14:45,685 --> 00:14:47,106
That the baby girl her dad threw away

288
00:14:47,106 --> 00:14:49,912
was never the ugly duckling,
but a swan all along.

289
00:14:49,912 --> 00:14:51,338
You want to make him see that.

290
00:14:51,338 --> 00:14:52,586
Am I wrong?

291
00:14:53,754 --> 00:14:55,290
I warned you once.

292
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:57,391
Not to act like you know me.

293
00:14:59,939 --> 00:15:01,462
What?

294
00:15:01,462 --> 00:15:02,496
You frightened?

295
00:15:02,496 --> 00:15:04,894
That I'll run straight to the presidents
and spill it all?

296
00:15:04,894 --> 00:15:07,168
Then you'd never set foot on Korean soil again.

297
00:15:07,168 --> 00:15:09,097
And you'd never get to see your mom either.

298
00:15:09,097 --> 00:15:10,771
Right.

299
00:15:10,771 --> 00:15:11,772
Hold on now!

300
00:15:11,772 --> 00:15:14,173
Or does your mom get tossed out too,
from the Kang house?

301
00:15:14,173 --> 00:15:16,333
- Hwang Jun Hyeon!
- Get your head on straight.

302
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,033
If you want that flimsy little plan to work.

303
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:20,247
Then learn what you've got to do from here.

304
00:15:21,593 --> 00:15:24,518
The chairman swore he'd never
hand Choiseong to them.

305
00:15:24,518 --> 00:15:27,538
He asked me to recover
the money those two stole.

306
00:15:27,538 --> 00:15:29,623
The person you should team up with.

307
00:15:30,639 --> 00:15:32,459
That'd be me.

308
00:15:34,639 --> 00:15:36,731
At least with this money,

309
00:15:36,731 --> 00:15:39,072
I'm all set to stab the presidents in the back.

310
00:15:39,072 --> 00:15:40,338
By what means, exactly.

311
00:15:40,338 --> 00:15:42,437
I've already kicked it off.

312
00:15:42,437 --> 00:15:44,817
That intern PT presentation.

313
00:15:44,817 --> 00:15:47,074
It's the trap to snare Jae Seong.

314
00:15:59,239 --> 00:16:01,756
<i>The ones who shattered my leg
and killed my career.</i>

315
00:16:01,756 --> 00:16:03,034
<i>It was your sister and brother.</i>

316
00:16:03,034 --> 00:16:07,895
<i>You're sure the twins saw Chairman Kang last?</i>

317
00:16:13,972 --> 00:16:16,705
<i>Are you trying to get killed by your siblings?</i>

318
00:16:16,705 --> 00:16:19,373
<i>You promised to stay away from Choiseong.</i>

319
00:16:20,918 --> 00:16:22,743
<i>Get your head on straight.</i>

320
00:16:22,743 --> 00:16:24,699
<i>If you want that flimsy little plan to work.</i>

321
00:16:24,699 --> 00:16:26,914
<i>Then learn what you've got to do from here.</i>

322
00:16:51,939 --> 00:16:56,211
Has it been fifteen years?

323
00:16:56,944 --> 00:16:59,479
I'm looking forward to this.

324
00:17:00,527 --> 00:17:02,650
Was this agreed upon?

325
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:05,186
She said she just wanted her mom's cooking.

326
00:17:05,186 --> 00:17:06,955
You don't have to mind at all.

327
00:17:06,955 --> 00:17:09,023
Until the succession is done.

328
00:17:09,023 --> 00:17:10,839
Let's keep her on a tight leash.

329
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:12,572
- Your sister said that?
- Yeah.

330
00:17:12,572 --> 00:17:14,206
No, she didn't.

331
00:17:14,206 --> 00:17:15,462
I told her she could stay here.

332
00:17:15,462 --> 00:17:17,933
The eldest son makes
all those choices, you know.

333
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,603
Where's Mom?

334
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:25,472
She is cleaning up your room,

335
00:17:25,472 --> 00:17:27,174
Housekeeper Jo.

336
00:17:28,742 --> 00:17:31,946
Why is grandma Housekeeper Jo?

337
00:17:31,946 --> 00:17:34,316
She used to be the maid in our house.

338
00:17:34,316 --> 00:17:35,980
Unbelievable.

339
00:17:35,980 --> 00:17:37,539
Is that right, Mom?

340
00:17:37,539 --> 00:17:41,623
If it's the absolute truth,
the word is "obviously."

341
00:17:41,623 --> 00:17:43,258
Oh, right.

342
00:17:43,258 --> 00:17:45,125
Obviously.

343
00:17:47,405 --> 00:17:49,158
Bang Geul, you're here?

344
00:17:49,158 --> 00:17:52,178
Mom, why are you wearing that?

345
00:17:52,178 --> 00:17:53,834
I had her do some cleaning up.

346
00:17:53,834 --> 00:17:55,603
You two should share the same room.

347
00:17:55,603 --> 00:17:58,605
With Father not here, it's not right for her

348
00:17:58,605 --> 00:18:00,307
to take the master bed.

349
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:03,405
You've been apart for so long,

350
00:18:03,405 --> 00:18:06,906
it will be nice to stick so close.

351
00:18:06,906 --> 00:18:08,615
Don't you agree?

352
00:18:11,464 --> 00:18:15,023
I did a deep clean of the house
before your dad gets back.

353
00:18:15,023 --> 00:18:17,115
It works out perfectly.

354
00:18:23,899 --> 00:18:25,872
Is my room

355
00:18:25,872 --> 00:18:27,539
exactly the same?

356
00:18:27,539 --> 00:18:29,002
Of course.

357
00:18:40,639 --> 00:18:43,784
We definitely need to get a brand new bed.

358
00:18:45,953 --> 00:18:49,457
Let's just share my blanket for the time being.

359
00:18:49,457 --> 00:18:52,006
Mine is a lot cozier.

360
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,994
- Mom.
- Yeah?

361
00:18:57,173 --> 00:18:59,437
Mom.

362
00:18:59,437 --> 00:19:01,101
What?

363
00:19:02,803 --> 00:19:05,907
If you want out of this house,
say so right now.

364
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:11,058
Where would I go? This is our home.

365
00:19:11,058 --> 00:19:13,680
And your father will wake up soon enough.

366
00:19:15,639 --> 00:19:17,317
You're really okay with this?

367
00:19:19,705 --> 00:19:23,471
I've lived in this house for thirty years.

368
00:19:23,471 --> 00:19:25,692
If I leave, I'll walk out on my own.

369
00:19:28,696 --> 00:19:31,772
I'll hold you close every single night now.

370
00:19:31,772 --> 00:19:33,701
I couldn't be happier.

371
00:19:33,701 --> 00:19:35,227
Oh, my girl.

372
00:19:35,227 --> 00:19:36,820
I feel the same.

373
00:19:36,820 --> 00:19:40,107
It's so good to hold my daughter again.

374
00:19:55,906 --> 00:19:57,824
What are you looking around for?

375
00:19:59,999 --> 00:20:03,133
The place feels so empty to me.

376
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:06,032
Most homes have a family photo up, right?

377
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:10,305
That's a normal home, though.

378
00:20:10,305 --> 00:20:12,399
And we're nothing like that.

379
00:20:12,399 --> 00:20:14,875
Thanks to you and your mother.

380
00:20:20,472 --> 00:20:24,033
I'm honestly just curious here.

381
00:20:24,033 --> 00:20:27,106
What's the real reason you came back here?

382
00:20:27,106 --> 00:20:29,389
Are you out for some kind of payback?

383
00:20:32,373 --> 00:20:33,459
Me?

384
00:20:33,459 --> 00:20:35,873
Against you?

385
00:20:35,873 --> 00:20:37,054
Payback? Hardly.

386
00:20:37,054 --> 00:20:41,369
I'm so grateful you took me in,
I could bow at your feet.

387
00:20:41,369 --> 00:20:42,853
I mean it.

388
00:20:42,853 --> 00:20:45,472
Don't try pulling anything.

389
00:20:45,472 --> 00:20:47,674
And quit clinging to me like this.

390
00:20:47,674 --> 00:20:50,066
Stay out of sight as much as you can.

391
00:20:50,066 --> 00:20:52,981
Keep your head down like you always have.

392
00:20:52,981 --> 00:20:54,729
You're so good at that, after all.

393
00:20:57,039 --> 00:21:00,053
That's the only way
you'll cling to this house at all.

394
00:21:03,091 --> 00:21:05,025
Of course.

395
00:21:05,025 --> 00:21:07,513
I'll do whatever you tell me to.

396
00:21:07,513 --> 00:21:10,330
At the office later, we never cross paths.

397
00:21:12,572 --> 00:21:15,133
Just hold on a little longer, Mom.

398
00:21:15,133 --> 00:21:17,704
I'll make them pay for every bit of it.

399
00:21:18,605 --> 00:21:21,034
Manager, have you seen this yet?

400
00:21:21,034 --> 00:21:22,274
I'm looking at it right now.

401
00:21:22,274 --> 00:21:24,472
<i>I hereby order this.</i>

402
00:21:24,472 --> 00:21:26,146
- Chairman...
<i>- From this moment on,</i>

403
00:21:26,146 --> 00:21:29,967
<i>there will be no bloodline succession.</i>

404
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:35,175
<i>Every Choiseong employee has
the right to become chairman.</i>

405
00:21:35,175 --> 00:21:37,024
<i>Until I return,</i>

406
00:21:37,024 --> 00:21:40,794
<i>Lee Sang Jae of Strategic Planning</i>

407
00:21:40,794 --> 00:21:44,431
<i>will serve as acting chairman.</i>

408
00:21:55,006 --> 00:21:58,472
We've confirmed
Manager Jang Moon Ho entered Spain.

409
00:21:58,472 --> 00:21:59,646
<i>What happened here?</i>

410
00:21:59,646 --> 00:22:02,861
<i>The motor sounded off,
so I sent it to the shop.</i>

411
00:22:02,861 --> 00:22:04,751
Send Team Leader Jo from Audit.

412
00:22:04,751 --> 00:22:07,401
He's bound to be holding
proof tied to the accident.

413
00:22:07,401 --> 00:22:09,456
Yes, I'll pass that along.

414
00:22:14,006 --> 00:22:17,098
Chairman, please wake up soon.

415
00:22:17,098 --> 00:22:20,335
Until then, Choiseong and this seat,

416
00:22:20,335 --> 00:22:23,236
I'll guard them with my life.

417
00:22:38,218 --> 00:22:39,232
[Hwang Jun Hyeon]

418
00:22:43,123 --> 00:22:44,271
[Casey Kang]

419
00:22:48,352 --> 00:22:50,330
So you showed up to work just fine?

420
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:51,499
I figured you'd go home, take a beating,

421
00:22:51,499 --> 00:22:53,693
then get shipped off or locked up somewhere.

422
00:22:53,693 --> 00:22:55,468
I still don't trust you.

423
00:22:57,391 --> 00:22:59,174
So go ahead and prove it.

424
00:22:59,174 --> 00:23:01,637
That you can really take down Kang Jae Seong.

425
00:23:05,479 --> 00:23:07,761
A little early to celebrate, isn't it?

426
00:23:09,906 --> 00:23:13,053
I've tossed a stone into calm waters,

427
00:23:13,053 --> 00:23:14,921
so the ripples are bound to spread.

428
00:23:22,705 --> 00:23:24,565
[Field Inventory In and Out Log]
The tsunami's hit,

429
00:23:24,565 --> 00:23:27,400
so the sharks in hiding will start surfacing.

430
00:23:29,037 --> 00:23:30,388
Is something going on?

431
00:23:30,388 --> 00:23:32,405
The Sales jerks are acting up again.

432
00:23:32,405 --> 00:23:34,818
We close inventory this week
and they won't cooperate.

433
00:23:34,818 --> 00:23:35,869
They won't even pick up the phone.

434
00:23:35,869 --> 00:23:37,544
Hand me the list, I'll help out too.

435
00:23:37,544 --> 00:23:40,614
- And Mr. Hwang, you too...
- Yes, this is Materials Team 2.

436
00:23:40,614 --> 00:23:43,206
The settlement files from Sales Team 3
still haven't come in.

437
00:23:43,206 --> 00:23:45,953
<i>Look, I said I'll send them.</i>

438
00:23:45,953 --> 00:23:47,273
<i>So quit breathing down my neck.</i>

439
00:23:47,273 --> 00:23:48,672
No files by the day after tomorrow,

440
00:23:48,672 --> 00:23:51,550
I'll leave Sales blank.

441
00:23:51,550 --> 00:23:53,379
<i>Excuse me?</i>

442
00:23:53,379 --> 00:23:54,991
<i>Hey, who do you think you are?</i>

443
00:23:54,991 --> 00:23:57,599
Watch how you talk to me.

444
00:23:57,599 --> 00:23:59,199
Well, what else can I do?

445
00:23:59,199 --> 00:24:01,435
You won't send the files,
so I'll file the report with blanks.

446
00:24:01,435 --> 00:24:03,290
Should I just make the numbers up?

447
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:05,290
That wouldn't be right, would it?

448
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:07,071
- What's wrong with him?
- No idea.

449
00:24:07,071 --> 00:24:09,239
Either way, we close out
the day after tomorrow,

450
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:11,511
so after that, it's your problem to deal with.

451
00:24:11,511 --> 00:24:13,246
I'll hang up now.

452
00:24:22,768 --> 00:24:24,258
Why's everyone staring at me?

453
00:24:24,258 --> 00:24:25,941
Blanks?

454
00:24:25,941 --> 00:24:28,028
No, the Sales team, this is...

455
00:24:28,028 --> 00:24:29,930
There's clueless, and then there's you.

456
00:24:29,930 --> 00:24:33,060
Who handed him a phone?
I said give him nothing to do.

457
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:35,068
Manager Park Bong Gi.

458
00:24:36,739 --> 00:24:40,107
There are a few things in life
that really wear you down,

459
00:24:40,107 --> 00:24:41,572
and the one that burns me up the most

460
00:24:41,572 --> 00:24:44,611
is some guy no better than me standing over me.

461
00:24:44,611 --> 00:24:46,413
Is everyone here

462
00:24:46,413 --> 00:24:48,764
really behind those Sales guys
in school, résumé, and raw skill?

463
00:24:48,764 --> 00:24:51,918
So why do you keep getting dragged
around by Sales?

464
00:24:54,842 --> 00:24:58,437
Sales lording it over the Materials team?

465
00:24:58,437 --> 00:25:01,061
Who decided that pecking order
in the first place?

466
00:25:02,372 --> 00:25:05,899
In the chairman's eyes,
at least, we're all the same.

467
00:25:08,039 --> 00:25:10,937
Just employees, every one of us.

468
00:25:11,638 --> 00:25:14,797
What's that got to do with the mess you caused?

469
00:25:14,797 --> 00:25:17,044
Right, why are you dodging the point?

470
00:25:17,044 --> 00:25:18,539
If you want to find out who's really tough,

471
00:25:18,539 --> 00:25:20,649
you push them to the edge of the cliff.

472
00:25:20,649 --> 00:25:22,910
You see which guy goes over,

473
00:25:22,910 --> 00:25:25,819
and which guy hangs on.

474
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:30,590
Let's step aside and talk in private.

475
00:25:31,591 --> 00:25:33,193
[Meeting Room]

476
00:25:33,193 --> 00:25:35,662
I ran the numbers
before I pushed them to the edge,

477
00:25:35,662 --> 00:25:37,764
so there's no need to worry.

478
00:25:39,939 --> 00:25:41,068
What numbers?

479
00:25:41,068 --> 00:25:42,535
Here's the thing.

480
00:25:44,239 --> 00:25:46,006
For a company, efficiency comes first.

481
00:25:46,006 --> 00:25:48,675
Rather than fight
this absurd battle every month,

482
00:25:48,675 --> 00:25:52,050
we're better off cutting
the middleman out entirely.

483
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,273
From now on, Materials skips Sales

484
00:25:54,273 --> 00:25:57,004
and pulls inventory straight from the vendors.

485
00:25:58,705 --> 00:26:00,320
Jun Hyeon.

486
00:26:01,690 --> 00:26:03,207
The thing is,

487
00:26:04,726 --> 00:26:07,796
I'm a man who just wants a quiet life.

488
00:26:07,796 --> 00:26:09,830
Conflict, infighting,

489
00:26:09,830 --> 00:26:12,366
I hate it more than anything in this world.

490
00:26:12,366 --> 00:26:16,471
Couldn't you just go to Sales and apologize?

491
00:26:19,005 --> 00:26:20,954
Do you know how many vendors there are?

492
00:26:20,954 --> 00:26:21,994
More than a thousand!

493
00:26:21,994 --> 00:26:23,539
They're just vendors.

494
00:26:23,539 --> 00:26:25,412
Give them the template to fill out,

495
00:26:25,412 --> 00:26:26,880
and it's done in a single day.

496
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,605
Besides, Materials answers to Support,

497
00:26:29,605 --> 00:26:32,354
so if files come in late,
Support just freezes their funding.

498
00:26:32,354 --> 00:26:34,239
What is there to worry about?

499
00:26:34,239 --> 00:26:35,789
Well...

500
00:26:35,789 --> 00:26:38,191
But to handle all of that,
we don't have the headcount...

501
00:26:38,191 --> 00:26:39,472
Then bring more people on.

502
00:26:39,472 --> 00:26:43,206
Staffing's only short at closing,
so there's no way they'd fill...

503
00:26:43,206 --> 00:26:45,254
Why on earth do I keep answering you?

504
00:26:45,254 --> 00:26:48,584
Look, we'll take care of the closing ourselves,

505
00:26:48,584 --> 00:26:50,537
so hire some temps.

506
00:26:52,506 --> 00:26:54,338
More work means a bigger team,

507
00:26:54,338 --> 00:26:57,605
a bigger team means respect
and faster promotions.

508
00:26:57,605 --> 00:26:59,646
That's just the basics.

509
00:27:04,184 --> 00:27:06,096
It was you, wasn't it?

510
00:27:06,096 --> 00:27:08,983
Who taught you to answer the phone so rudely?

511
00:27:08,983 --> 00:27:11,257
Those Materials clowns, I swear!

512
00:27:12,372 --> 00:27:14,294
Well, sure.

513
00:27:14,294 --> 00:27:16,681
What's anyone learning under Manager Park?

514
00:27:16,681 --> 00:27:20,202
Best case, they end up some hire's errand boy.

515
00:27:20,202 --> 00:27:21,936
An errand boy?

516
00:27:22,561 --> 00:27:24,101
Manager...

517
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:25,538
It's not like that...

518
00:27:26,821 --> 00:27:29,443
The new kid set me off, that's all.

519
00:27:29,443 --> 00:27:32,279
You're the one who tossed
your manners out the window.

520
00:27:32,279 --> 00:27:34,281
Your boss looks down on me
for being a special hire.

521
00:27:34,281 --> 00:27:36,716
So now even you are stepping out of line?

522
00:27:40,854 --> 00:27:42,134
Where are your manners?

523
00:27:42,134 --> 00:27:44,162
A moment like this calls for an apology.

524
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:45,454
These young guys.

525
00:27:45,454 --> 00:27:47,560
I can't make sense of them.

526
00:27:48,906 --> 00:27:50,214
Do I look like a joke?

527
00:27:50,214 --> 00:27:52,466
No, sir. Not at all.

528
00:27:52,466 --> 00:27:54,684
We shouldn't just let
an insult like this slide.

529
00:27:54,684 --> 00:27:56,813
Report this straight

530
00:27:56,813 --> 00:27:58,271
to the Managing Director.

531
00:28:01,208 --> 00:28:03,724
[Business Cooperation Request]

532
00:28:05,078 --> 00:28:09,050
So you're saying you want
to go head-to-head with Sales?

533
00:28:09,050 --> 00:28:10,417
Yes.

534
00:28:10,417 --> 00:28:12,072
Checking their inventory status
and handing it over

535
00:28:12,072 --> 00:28:13,820
really isn't that hard of a job.

536
00:28:13,820 --> 00:28:16,006
I'm certain some of them are inflating prices

537
00:28:16,006 --> 00:28:17,891
or secretly getting illegal kickbacks
on the side.

538
00:28:17,891 --> 00:28:19,761
And you think you can win?

539
00:28:20,942 --> 00:28:23,632
You're messing
with the President's inner circle.

540
00:28:23,632 --> 00:28:26,699
If we make one wrong move,
we'll lose everything.

541
00:28:30,438 --> 00:28:32,295
Tell me the truth.

542
00:28:32,295 --> 00:28:34,240
This isn't your own idea.

543
00:28:35,060 --> 00:28:37,077
You're always playing it so incredibly safe,

544
00:28:37,077 --> 00:28:39,139
you'd wash water before drinking it.

545
00:28:39,139 --> 00:28:42,516
No way you'd drop a massive bomb
like this on your own.

546
00:28:42,516 --> 00:28:43,552
Who is it?

547
00:28:43,552 --> 00:28:45,086
Who put you up to this crazy stunt?

548
00:28:45,086 --> 00:28:47,320
Well, it's...

549
00:28:53,139 --> 00:28:54,995
Hello.

550
00:28:54,995 --> 00:28:57,699
I'm Hwang Jun Hyeon,
the newbie on Materials Team 2.

551
00:28:59,972 --> 00:29:02,469
Are you guys pulling some kind of joke on me?

552
00:29:02,469 --> 00:29:04,905
You listened to a clueless rookie
who knows nothing,

553
00:29:04,905 --> 00:29:07,540
and created this huge mess?

554
00:29:08,243 --> 00:29:09,442
I'm so sorry.

555
00:29:09,442 --> 00:29:12,766
I must have completely
lost my mind for a second. I apologize.

556
00:29:12,766 --> 00:29:16,115
Are you afraid to get
into a power struggle with Sales?

557
00:29:17,624 --> 00:29:18,374
What?

558
00:29:18,374 --> 00:29:21,054
Or do you simply have no idea
what's really at stake here?

559
00:29:21,054 --> 00:29:22,789
Shut up.

560
00:29:22,789 --> 00:29:25,760
I'll make sure to discipline him properly.

561
00:29:26,693 --> 00:29:29,106
What's really at stake?

562
00:29:29,106 --> 00:29:30,787
And you claim to know?

563
00:29:30,787 --> 00:29:33,168
Sales and Management,
the two pillars of Trading.

564
00:29:33,168 --> 00:29:36,879
It's a battle to see which of them
grabs the upper hand.

565
00:29:36,879 --> 00:29:38,539
Sales rules the roost now.

566
00:29:38,539 --> 00:29:41,507
We must step up and grab the reins.

567
00:29:42,142 --> 00:29:45,445
We're a trading company.
Our entire focus is on sales.

568
00:29:45,445 --> 00:29:48,539
It's only natural for the Sales department
to hold the power.

569
00:29:48,539 --> 00:29:49,628
Don't you even know that?

570
00:29:49,628 --> 00:29:51,084
That made sense when we were growing rapidly,

571
00:29:51,084 --> 00:29:53,889
but right now,
Trading has completely hit its limit.

572
00:29:53,889 --> 00:29:56,222
Revenue's been stuck
at five trillion for years now,

573
00:29:56,222 --> 00:29:58,328
so management's role is
becoming much more crucial.

574
00:29:58,328 --> 00:30:00,806
Trying to get their stories straight
delays the reports,

575
00:30:00,806 --> 00:30:03,405
and if they're actually faking
the inventory numbers,

576
00:30:03,405 --> 00:30:05,332
it's not just a personal crime.

577
00:30:05,332 --> 00:30:06,666
It's corporate fraud.

578
00:30:06,666 --> 00:30:07,834
Please, just stop.

579
00:30:07,834 --> 00:30:09,037
Keep talking.

580
00:30:09,037 --> 00:30:11,704
Those subcontractors belong to someone here.

581
00:30:12,793 --> 00:30:15,177
Could be an executive's firm,

582
00:30:15,177 --> 00:30:17,610
or even the President's.

583
00:30:18,505 --> 00:30:22,688
<i>Cut ties with Yujin Networks, IB Global,
and Hwain Dynamics.</i>

584
00:30:22,688 --> 00:30:27,153
<i>That brings in over 30 billion won
in net profit each year.</i>

585
00:30:28,688 --> 00:30:32,127
<i>Does this kid actually know what he's saying?</i>

586
00:30:32,127 --> 00:30:34,227
Director Lee Sang Jae is acting chairman now.

587
00:30:34,227 --> 00:30:37,138
Isn't the timing perfect?

588
00:30:37,138 --> 00:30:39,799
He's totally clean regarding this stuff,

589
00:30:39,799 --> 00:30:43,102
so he'll take your side if this blows up.

590
00:30:45,818 --> 00:30:48,106
Bong Gi, listen.

591
00:30:48,106 --> 00:30:50,972
This could cost you your job.

592
00:30:50,972 --> 00:30:52,779
I just...

593
00:30:53,413 --> 00:30:55,382
He'll do great.

594
00:30:55,382 --> 00:30:57,839
To everyone who looked
down on you as a special hire,

595
00:30:57,839 --> 00:31:00,353
this is your chance to show them who you are.

596
00:31:02,939 --> 00:31:06,092
Not just my job. My life's on the line.

597
00:31:06,862 --> 00:31:09,747
I'll show 'em what a special hire can do.

598
00:31:16,642 --> 00:31:18,534
Send the notice.

599
00:31:18,534 --> 00:31:21,608
To Director Song and all of Sales.

600
00:31:21,608 --> 00:31:23,109
Yes, sir.

601
00:31:35,539 --> 00:31:37,290
Manager!

602
00:31:40,267 --> 00:31:42,438
Built like a total mountain,

603
00:31:42,438 --> 00:31:45,018
what a total waste.

604
00:31:45,018 --> 00:31:47,100
He's been through a lot.

605
00:31:48,868 --> 00:31:51,391
Manager Park used to be on the Audit Team.

606
00:31:51,391 --> 00:31:52,398
[Audit Team Deputy Head Park Bong Gi]

607
00:31:52,398 --> 00:31:54,040
<i>During an audit five years ago,</i>

608
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:57,277
<i>President Kang Jae Seong's
illegal overseas real estate investments...</i>

609
00:31:57,277 --> 00:31:59,212
<i>he was the ace who caught it.</i>

610
00:31:59,212 --> 00:32:02,601
He got demoted here to cover it all up.

611
00:32:02,601 --> 00:32:05,752
Is that why he's playing it safe?

612
00:32:05,752 --> 00:32:08,141
Amazing that he still comes to work.

613
00:32:08,141 --> 00:32:10,290
Why did the chairman
even cover for that awful kid?

614
00:32:10,290 --> 00:32:12,640
He's just going to get backstabbed.

615
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,461
He should treat his loyal staff better.

616
00:32:14,461 --> 00:32:17,330
Execs treating us like disposable trash...

617
00:32:17,330 --> 00:32:18,497
We have to fix this.

618
00:32:18,497 --> 00:32:20,161
Why would anyone stay loyal...

619
00:32:20,161 --> 00:32:21,421
What's with that look?

620
00:32:21,421 --> 00:32:23,134
Still, calling the bosses trash...

621
00:32:23,134 --> 00:32:23,901
What?

622
00:32:23,901 --> 00:32:25,739
Our Casey knows how to get mad.

623
00:32:25,739 --> 00:32:26,741
Manager!

624
00:32:26,741 --> 00:32:28,741
You should lie down and rest.

625
00:32:29,494 --> 00:32:30,541
I look like I've aged ten years, right?

626
00:32:30,541 --> 00:32:31,653
Yeah.

627
00:32:31,653 --> 00:32:33,279
It's all because of that punk.

628
00:32:33,279 --> 00:32:36,015
Did he drug me or cast a spell?

629
00:32:36,015 --> 00:32:37,273
Whenever I talk to him,

630
00:32:37,273 --> 00:32:40,806
I end up doing crazy things like I'm possessed.

631
00:32:40,806 --> 00:32:44,023
It's not terminal, so please don't worry.

632
00:32:45,605 --> 00:32:47,560
You slept comfortably.

633
00:32:50,415 --> 00:32:52,534
Excuse me.

634
00:32:52,534 --> 00:32:54,102
- Hello?
- What the...

635
00:32:55,006 --> 00:32:57,937
<i>Hello, is this Hwang Jun Hyeon's phone?</i>

636
00:32:57,937 --> 00:32:59,605
Yes, who is this?

637
00:32:59,605 --> 00:33:01,241
<i>If you changed your number,</i>

638
00:33:01,241 --> 00:33:03,503
<i>you should've told us!</i>

639
00:33:03,503 --> 00:33:05,378
I saw the news you joined Choiseong,

640
00:33:05,378 --> 00:33:07,486
and called them to track you down.

641
00:33:07,486 --> 00:33:09,048
Aren't you worried about Grandma?

642
00:33:09,048 --> 00:33:10,150
Grandma?

643
00:33:10,150 --> 00:33:11,818
<i>All the pain I put her through,</i>

644
00:33:11,818 --> 00:33:15,755
<i>every drop of sweat I left on that field,
can you price that?</i>

645
00:33:17,438 --> 00:33:18,825
I'm a little busy right now.

646
00:33:18,825 --> 00:33:20,883
Are you really Jun Hyeon?

647
00:33:20,883 --> 00:33:23,643
<i>Your beloved grandma went missing!</i>

648
00:33:23,643 --> 00:33:26,183
<i>She vanished while I was in the restroom.</i>

649
00:33:26,183 --> 00:33:29,472
- Then you should call the cops first.
<i>- I did!</i>

650
00:33:29,472 --> 00:33:32,464
We just checked all the cameras.

651
00:33:32,464 --> 00:33:34,717
We think she went to see you.

652
00:33:34,717 --> 00:33:38,211
<i>She took a bus to Seoul.</i>

653
00:33:38,211 --> 00:33:40,206
Get to the terminal now!

654
00:33:40,206 --> 00:33:43,683
It's before quitting time, so I can't.

655
00:33:45,539 --> 00:33:47,753
Didn't she say your grandma's missing?

656
00:33:49,116 --> 00:33:51,157
Hurry up and go, punk!

657
00:33:52,828 --> 00:33:54,427
Taxi!

658
00:33:58,531 --> 00:34:01,972
She'll instantly know I'm not her grandson.

659
00:34:01,972 --> 00:34:04,136
I can't get exposed already.

660
00:34:04,939 --> 00:34:06,730
Hey, taxi!

661
00:34:06,730 --> 00:34:08,541
Come on.

662
00:34:14,981 --> 00:34:16,090
Get in.

663
00:34:16,090 --> 00:34:17,884
Hey, are you slacking off too?

664
00:34:17,884 --> 00:34:19,039
Stay back and handle the...

665
00:34:19,039 --> 00:34:22,355
What kind of absolute lunatic are you?

666
00:34:22,355 --> 00:34:26,013
Should I really team up
with this arrogant bastard or what?

667
00:34:26,013 --> 00:34:27,023
Get in, now!

668
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:29,023
Hey, why are you so mad?

669
00:34:29,023 --> 00:34:30,396
Not even your business.

670
00:34:30,396 --> 00:34:31,989
Geez.

671
00:34:43,039 --> 00:34:45,044
MD Kwon sent a notice?

672
00:34:45,044 --> 00:34:46,084
Why?

673
00:34:46,084 --> 00:34:48,150
It's a declaration of war.

674
00:34:48,150 --> 00:34:51,273
He knows exactly what messing
with subcontractors means.

675
00:34:51,273 --> 00:34:54,979
Is President Kang Jae Gyeong
pulling the strings?

676
00:34:56,370 --> 00:35:00,593
It's definitely unsettling
she knows about my slush fund.

677
00:35:02,173 --> 00:35:04,898
I think we should take the overseas accounts

678
00:35:04,898 --> 00:35:06,833
and swap them all out right now.

679
00:35:06,833 --> 00:35:08,705
Do we really have to go that far?

680
00:35:08,705 --> 00:35:10,870
The battle for shares starts soon.

681
00:35:10,870 --> 00:35:12,405
Bringing the funds to Korea

682
00:35:12,405 --> 00:35:14,540
to secure more shares would be smart.

683
00:35:15,936 --> 00:35:17,410
Handle it cleanly.

684
00:35:17,410 --> 00:35:19,317
As fast as possible.

685
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:20,613
Don't worry, President.

686
00:35:20,613 --> 00:35:22,415
I trust you.

687
00:35:25,372 --> 00:35:26,819
I'm on my way.

688
00:35:28,988 --> 00:35:31,273
<i>He gave the green light.</i>

689
00:35:31,273 --> 00:35:34,827
<i>I'll liquidate the slush fund
as you instructed.</i>

690
00:35:36,338 --> 00:35:38,533
He's two minutes late.

691
00:35:38,533 --> 00:35:40,767
His father is always so punctual.

692
00:35:40,767 --> 00:35:43,603
Who does he take after?

693
00:35:43,603 --> 00:35:45,171
Thanks to that, we get our foot in the door

694
00:35:45,171 --> 00:35:46,773
for the Yuncheon Port Project too.

695
00:35:46,773 --> 00:35:49,409
If he fails to become Chairman,

696
00:35:49,409 --> 00:35:52,872
there's no reason to keep him around.

697
00:35:52,872 --> 00:35:54,881
Don't you worry.

698
00:35:54,881 --> 00:35:56,718
Before I'm Choiseong's daughter-in-law,

699
00:35:56,718 --> 00:35:58,918
I'm a daughter of Taeha first.

700
00:36:03,987 --> 00:36:06,193
Oh my goodness. Sorry I'm late.

701
00:36:06,193 --> 00:36:08,396
Glad you made it.

702
00:36:08,396 --> 00:36:09,993
Have you been well?

703
00:36:11,397 --> 00:36:13,097
You're here? Here.

704
00:36:13,097 --> 00:36:15,068
Thank you.

705
00:36:15,068 --> 00:36:18,037
Any problems at the company?

706
00:36:20,273 --> 00:36:22,052
Not at all.

707
00:36:22,052 --> 00:36:23,732
Nothing at all.

708
00:36:23,732 --> 00:36:26,573
Exactly as planned, I've arranged for Taeha

709
00:36:26,573 --> 00:36:29,892
to naturally join
the consortium as a latecomer.

710
00:36:29,892 --> 00:36:33,419
Heard your youngest sister just joined Trading.

711
00:36:37,303 --> 00:36:40,093
You seriously don't have to worry about her.

712
00:36:40,093 --> 00:36:41,730
She's an absolute nobody.

713
00:36:41,730 --> 00:36:45,605
Since all of Father's shares
go to the next Chairman,

714
00:36:45,605 --> 00:36:48,701
once this port project wraps up successfully,

715
00:36:48,701 --> 00:36:51,837
the entire board will take my side.

716
00:36:52,605 --> 00:36:54,505
The Yuncheon Mayor,

717
00:36:54,505 --> 00:36:56,209
is he an old classmate of yours?

718
00:36:56,209 --> 00:36:58,077
They're basically best friends for life.

719
00:36:58,077 --> 00:37:01,180
We sent some paintings to his wife too.

720
00:37:02,015 --> 00:37:04,083
I'll strike a deal with the civic groups soon,

721
00:37:04,083 --> 00:37:06,321
and officially sign the papers.

722
00:37:06,321 --> 00:37:07,820
Kang Jae Gyeong?

723
00:37:07,820 --> 00:37:09,422
She's no match for me.

724
00:37:09,422 --> 00:37:13,018
Guess I'll truly benefit from my son-in-law.

725
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:24,336
- Have a safe trip back home.
- I will.

726
00:37:32,078 --> 00:37:34,472
Why did you say something so useless to him

727
00:37:34,472 --> 00:37:36,218
and make a fool out of me?

728
00:37:36,218 --> 00:37:38,651
Especially at a critical time.

729
00:37:38,651 --> 00:37:40,720
We're family, so what's the big deal?

730
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:44,490
Now, my father is
the only father you have left.

731
00:37:44,490 --> 00:37:46,225
Once you become Chairman,

732
00:37:46,225 --> 00:37:48,616
Choiseong and Taeha will join hands

733
00:37:48,616 --> 00:37:51,500
and become Korea's biggest corporation.

734
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:53,450
So you absolutely cannot

735
00:37:54,106 --> 00:37:56,368
let Kang Jae Gyeong snatch it away.

736
00:37:57,742 --> 00:38:01,574
She doesn't have a backer like I do,
so she can't win.

737
00:38:01,574 --> 00:38:03,924
Just ask your father

738
00:38:03,924 --> 00:38:06,539
to put all of his support behind me.

739
00:38:06,539 --> 00:38:08,214
Got it.

740
00:38:13,372 --> 00:38:15,754
Bowing so low he's folding like a flip phone.

741
00:38:18,305 --> 00:38:20,003
How is it?

742
00:38:20,003 --> 00:38:22,143
Think he's going to get better?

743
00:38:22,143 --> 00:38:24,764
He's in a coma, so it's tough,

744
00:38:24,764 --> 00:38:25,896
but I'll keep trying.

745
00:38:25,896 --> 00:38:28,134
Keep trying,

746
00:38:28,134 --> 00:38:30,338
but make sure he wakes up slowly.

747
00:38:30,338 --> 00:38:32,018
What?

748
00:38:32,018 --> 00:38:35,877
I need to hold Father's lifeline
to stay in the fight.

749
00:38:35,877 --> 00:38:39,342
If Jae Seong uses Taeha to become Chairman,

750
00:38:39,342 --> 00:38:40,879
will you take the blame?

751
00:38:40,879 --> 00:38:42,582
I'm a doctor.

752
00:38:42,582 --> 00:38:45,218
I can't pull a stunt like last time again.

753
00:38:45,218 --> 00:38:47,589
You shouldn't be doing
reckless things like that.

754
00:38:47,589 --> 00:38:49,488
If anyone happens to find out...

755
00:38:54,539 --> 00:38:56,529
Don't you even feel

756
00:38:57,672 --> 00:38:59,732
the slightest pity for me?

757
00:39:01,501 --> 00:39:04,871
Growing Chemicals,
I couldn't even breastfeed Il Jun,

758
00:39:04,871 --> 00:39:08,207
and I never went on vacation with you.

759
00:39:08,207 --> 00:39:11,210
I sacrificed everything
for this damn endless competition,

760
00:39:11,210 --> 00:39:14,413
and even though I was sick of it,
I gritted my teeth.

761
00:39:15,539 --> 00:39:19,318
All for the sake of you and Il Jun.

762
00:39:20,639 --> 00:39:21,687
I know, but...

763
00:39:21,687 --> 00:39:23,625
We're almost there.

764
00:39:24,659 --> 00:39:28,572
Father always trusted me way more
than Jae Seong anyway.

765
00:39:28,572 --> 00:39:30,663
You know that perfectly well.

766
00:39:32,505 --> 00:39:34,500
Honey...

767
00:39:39,091 --> 00:39:41,125
You'll help me, right?

768
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:46,979
Whatever I ask you to do.

769
00:39:49,539 --> 00:39:51,006
If this is...

770
00:39:51,006 --> 00:39:53,352
what you really truly want...

771
00:39:58,466 --> 00:40:01,303
Restrict all visits to Father for now,

772
00:40:01,303 --> 00:40:04,330
and only share updates with me.

773
00:40:09,605 --> 00:40:14,259
<i>You don't even have the right to die anymore.</i>

774
00:40:14,259 --> 00:40:16,909
<i>I'm the one who decides when.</i>

775
00:40:18,511 --> 00:40:20,650
[VIP Ward Authorized Personnel Only]

776
00:40:20,650 --> 00:40:21,814
MD Kwon from Trading

777
00:40:21,814 --> 00:40:24,149
[Business Cooperation Request]
has gone up against Director Song.

778
00:40:25,754 --> 00:40:28,069
I wonder if Jae Seong

779
00:40:28,806 --> 00:40:31,423
will be able to handle this.

780
00:40:38,228 --> 00:40:40,366
Where the hell is she?

781
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:44,539
Why would she come all the way here?

782
00:40:44,539 --> 00:40:46,076
You little punk.

783
00:40:46,076 --> 00:40:47,895
Just call her and find out where she is.

784
00:40:47,895 --> 00:40:49,875
I don't have her number.

785
00:40:50,776 --> 00:40:52,273
What about a photo?

786
00:40:52,273 --> 00:40:54,146
Show me what she looks like, hurry.

787
00:40:54,146 --> 00:40:55,191
I don't have one.

788
00:40:55,191 --> 00:40:57,016
Do you know anything at all?

789
00:40:57,016 --> 00:40:58,276
What's her name? Her age?

790
00:40:58,276 --> 00:41:00,195
Is she really your grandma?

791
00:41:01,839 --> 00:41:03,516
It's not like that...

792
00:41:03,516 --> 00:41:05,324
Hwang Jun Hyeon!

793
00:41:06,605 --> 00:41:08,560
There he is, your grandson.

794
00:41:09,855 --> 00:41:11,730
Isn't he your grandson?

795
00:41:15,772 --> 00:41:17,636
Grandma.

796
00:41:18,404 --> 00:41:20,803
She can't even recognize me.

797
00:41:20,803 --> 00:41:23,096
<i>She only knows you in uniform.</i>

798
00:41:23,096 --> 00:41:25,344
<i>Her dementia, you know.</i>

799
00:41:26,505 --> 00:41:28,481
Eat as much as you want.

800
00:41:28,481 --> 00:41:30,349
She has dementia?

801
00:41:47,039 --> 00:41:48,868
I really owe you for all this.

802
00:41:48,868 --> 00:41:50,739
It isn't much, but...

803
00:41:51,505 --> 00:41:53,898
Are you sure?

804
00:41:53,898 --> 00:41:55,507
Please, take it.

805
00:41:58,277 --> 00:42:00,448
When did you last wash this thing?

806
00:42:04,106 --> 00:42:05,751
Oh, my sweet boy.

807
00:42:05,751 --> 00:42:09,154
I waited forever for you.

808
00:42:11,338 --> 00:42:13,492
I was swamped.

809
00:42:13,492 --> 00:42:14,827
How did the game go today?

810
00:42:14,827 --> 00:42:15,839
Did you win?

811
00:42:15,839 --> 00:42:17,863
How many goals did you score?

812
00:42:24,704 --> 00:42:26,238
You scored three goals?

813
00:42:26,238 --> 00:42:27,340
Oh, that's my boy.

814
00:42:27,340 --> 00:42:29,705
There you go, so proud of you.

815
00:42:29,705 --> 00:42:31,644
I didn't score any.

816
00:42:31,644 --> 00:42:33,372
So no kisses, please.

817
00:42:33,372 --> 00:42:36,849
You're cute either way, cuter when you score.

818
00:42:36,849 --> 00:42:38,384
Hey, go start the car, hurry.

819
00:42:38,384 --> 00:42:39,618
Am I your chauffeur now?

820
00:42:39,618 --> 00:42:41,423
Just move it.

821
00:42:41,423 --> 00:42:42,755
Give her a kiss.

822
00:42:42,755 --> 00:42:44,183
You little brat, go start the car.

823
00:42:44,183 --> 00:42:45,491
Come on!

824
00:42:45,491 --> 00:42:47,529
What do you mean, come on?

825
00:42:47,529 --> 00:42:49,072
- Let go.
- You're adorable.

826
00:42:49,072 --> 00:42:50,796
Let go of me.

827
00:42:52,431 --> 00:42:54,672
Just send her back to her old place.

828
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:56,702
A new environment isn't good for her.

829
00:42:56,702 --> 00:42:58,438
Run the dementia screening for her,

830
00:42:58,438 --> 00:43:00,162
and check if there's anything else wrong,

831
00:43:00,162 --> 00:43:01,822
every detail, please don't miss anything.

832
00:43:01,822 --> 00:43:03,842
He's the one covering the bills.

833
00:43:05,273 --> 00:43:07,381
You stole plenty from my dad, didn't you?

834
00:43:07,381 --> 00:43:09,341
<i>That money's mine.</i>

835
00:43:09,341 --> 00:43:11,617
We'll run a full workup, don't worry.

836
00:43:11,617 --> 00:43:13,555
Thanks so much.

837
00:43:18,772 --> 00:43:20,372
You know,

838
00:43:20,372 --> 00:43:22,864
your grandma really must adore you.

839
00:43:22,864 --> 00:43:25,464
She hasn't let go of your hand once.

840
00:43:31,937 --> 00:43:34,157
Why won't it come loose?

841
00:43:34,157 --> 00:43:35,908
I'm jealous.

842
00:43:36,545 --> 00:43:38,379
My dad never...

843
00:43:39,614 --> 00:43:41,413
<i>Mom!</i>

844
00:43:42,372 --> 00:43:43,916
<i>- Get in.
- Bang Geul.</i>

845
00:43:43,916 --> 00:43:44,984
<i>Let's go.</i>

846
00:43:44,984 --> 00:43:47,419
<i>- No...
- Mom.</i>

847
00:43:52,072 --> 00:43:54,193
<i>- Mom.
- Bang Geul.</i>

848
00:43:55,239 --> 00:43:57,039
<i>Bang Geul, get in the car.</i>

849
00:43:57,039 --> 00:43:59,305
<i>No.</i>

850
00:43:59,305 --> 00:44:02,100
<i>I don't want to study abroad.</i>

851
00:44:08,739 --> 00:44:11,039
<i>I hate you, Dad.</i>

852
00:44:11,039 --> 00:44:13,078
<i>I really hate you.</i>

853
00:44:16,539 --> 00:44:18,150
He must've had his reasons.

854
00:44:18,150 --> 00:44:19,885
He wanted to keep you safe from your siblings,

855
00:44:19,885 --> 00:44:22,221
isn't that what your father was really doing?

856
00:44:22,221 --> 00:44:25,080
What dad feels good
about sending his baby girl away?

857
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:27,293
No father in the world wants that, you hear me?

858
00:44:27,293 --> 00:44:29,580
What, do you have a daughter stashed somewhere?

859
00:44:29,580 --> 00:44:32,539
Why are you defending him this hard?

860
00:44:32,539 --> 00:44:34,366
Aren't you heading home?

861
00:44:35,139 --> 00:44:37,069
There's someone I need to see first.

862
00:44:39,173 --> 00:44:41,773
How's Chairman Kang doing?

863
00:45:00,987 --> 00:45:04,497
The therapist keeps massaging him
to prevent stiffness,

864
00:45:04,497 --> 00:45:07,933
and we've stayed on top of his nutrients,
so nothing's worsened.

865
00:45:07,933 --> 00:45:12,307
Copy his chart and bring me
the full medication list.

866
00:45:12,307 --> 00:45:14,673
Report everyone who visits him each day,

867
00:45:14,673 --> 00:45:16,141
especially

868
00:45:16,141 --> 00:45:18,644
keep a close eye on Professor Min.

869
00:45:18,644 --> 00:45:21,113
If anything happens, call me right away.

870
00:45:21,113 --> 00:45:22,181
Yes.

871
00:45:22,181 --> 00:45:24,216
And also,

872
00:45:24,216 --> 00:45:27,685
about that camera you mentioned,

873
00:45:27,685 --> 00:45:30,289
I installed it up there.

874
00:45:30,289 --> 00:45:32,206
It's synced with the ECG monitor,

875
00:45:32,206 --> 00:45:34,893
so you'll get an alert if anything changes.

876
00:45:41,139 --> 00:45:43,440
Don't say a word about this to her.

877
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:44,903
Understood.

878
00:45:45,571 --> 00:45:47,139
<i>Don't you worry.</i>

879
00:45:47,139 --> 00:45:51,243
<i>I will never let you die
at the hands of my children.</i>

880
00:45:54,072 --> 00:45:55,914
Here.

881
00:45:56,827 --> 00:45:58,338
When his youngest daughter visits,

882
00:45:58,338 --> 00:46:01,420
please make sure she can see
Chairman Kang anytime.

883
00:46:01,420 --> 00:46:03,258
Oh, and also...

884
00:46:03,906 --> 00:46:05,658
my...

885
00:46:05,658 --> 00:46:07,739
my grandma too,

886
00:46:07,739 --> 00:46:09,745
please take good care of her.

887
00:46:10,932 --> 00:46:12,497
Of course.

888
00:46:27,996 --> 00:46:30,886
I'm searching
for a top coma specialist right now.

889
00:46:30,886 --> 00:46:32,438
Your father,

890
00:46:32,438 --> 00:46:34,686
I'll make sure he wakes up.

891
00:46:36,206 --> 00:46:39,088
Quit acting generous with my dad's money.

892
00:46:39,088 --> 00:46:41,196
Just tell me the next step.

893
00:46:41,196 --> 00:46:43,528
Let's smoke them out of the rabbit hole,

894
00:46:44,648 --> 00:46:47,065
so the head rabbit shows his face.

895
00:46:49,735 --> 00:46:51,720
[Materials Team 2]

896
00:47:12,505 --> 00:47:14,006
Do we really...

897
00:47:14,006 --> 00:47:16,033
need to audit the vendors in person?

898
00:47:16,033 --> 00:47:17,196
It's simple.

899
00:47:17,196 --> 00:47:19,438
We tear through the warehouse,
count every single item,

900
00:47:19,438 --> 00:47:21,889
and pull all the in-and-out records.

901
00:47:21,889 --> 00:47:24,273
Be ready to wreck the place.

902
00:47:25,438 --> 00:47:27,339
Why should I be taking orders from you?

903
00:47:27,339 --> 00:47:29,174
I'm a manager, you're the new hire.

904
00:47:29,174 --> 00:47:30,743
You said you'd stake your job on this.

905
00:47:30,743 --> 00:47:32,573
Bring Materials Team 3 along, and hit,

906
00:47:32,573 --> 00:47:34,946
just three places, that's all we need.

907
00:47:38,705 --> 00:47:40,352
Which three were they again?

908
00:47:40,352 --> 00:47:45,494
[Yujin Networks]

909
00:47:45,494 --> 00:47:48,288
There's a limit to this kind
of bullying, seriously.

910
00:47:48,288 --> 00:47:50,369
You're really going to dig through our books?

911
00:47:50,369 --> 00:47:51,830
You're not even from Sales.

912
00:47:51,830 --> 00:47:55,000
Pull your staff out and unlock the warehouse.

913
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:56,435
Once we verify the inventory,

914
00:47:56,435 --> 00:47:58,531
we'll quietly leave, I promise.

915
00:47:59,905 --> 00:48:01,373
Why didn't you hand over the inventory sooner,

916
00:48:01,373 --> 00:48:03,068
and let things get this bad, you idiot!

917
00:48:03,068 --> 00:48:04,910
Making the head office come out here, really?

918
00:48:04,910 --> 00:48:07,772
Look, please don't blow this up.

919
00:48:07,772 --> 00:48:09,615
I will file a formal complaint.

920
00:48:09,615 --> 00:48:12,584
If your rating tanks,
you lose our business, you know that?

921
00:48:12,584 --> 00:48:15,338
So let's just keep it
to checking the inventory.

922
00:48:15,338 --> 00:48:17,438
Open the door already.

923
00:48:17,438 --> 00:48:18,824
I can't, sir.

924
00:48:18,824 --> 00:48:20,367
Really, this isn't happening.

925
00:48:20,367 --> 00:48:21,368
I said open it.

926
00:48:21,368 --> 00:48:22,562
I said no.

927
00:48:22,562 --> 00:48:24,672
- Open it...
- No way...

928
00:48:24,672 --> 00:48:26,198
You can't.

929
00:48:28,870 --> 00:48:30,139
All right, today we...

930
00:48:30,139 --> 00:48:31,703
Get in there, now!

931
00:48:36,106 --> 00:48:37,338
Move it, get inside!

932
00:48:37,338 --> 00:48:39,244
Open this door over here.

933
00:48:41,246 --> 00:48:42,273
Well.

934
00:48:42,273 --> 00:48:44,717
The warehouse stock and the paperwork numbers

935
00:48:44,717 --> 00:48:46,176
won't match, guaranteed.

936
00:48:46,176 --> 00:48:48,476
But we didn't come here to check if they match.

937
00:48:48,476 --> 00:48:50,556
We need to nail down
exactly how big the gap is.

938
00:48:50,556 --> 00:48:51,990
- Got it?
- Yes, sir.

939
00:48:51,990 --> 00:48:53,225
Move it.

940
00:48:54,206 --> 00:48:55,727
Wait a second.

941
00:48:57,106 --> 00:48:59,567
Where did our two interns disappear to?

942
00:49:00,639 --> 00:49:02,801
The hell is going on?

943
00:49:08,689 --> 00:49:09,707
Director Song!

944
00:49:09,707 --> 00:49:11,043
We have a serious problem!

945
00:49:11,043 --> 00:49:13,212
[Choiseong Group Parking Lot]
[Manager Park Bong Gi]

946
00:49:13,212 --> 00:49:15,417
Goodness.

947
00:49:16,318 --> 00:49:19,985
That's his fifth call.
Are you sure we should ignore it?

948
00:49:19,985 --> 00:49:22,721
The guy we need to tail is someone else.

949
00:49:26,438 --> 00:49:27,993
Hey.

950
00:49:30,139 --> 00:49:31,972
Director Song Nam Hoon?

951
00:49:31,972 --> 00:49:34,438
He's the one handling Jae Seong's slush fund.

952
00:49:34,438 --> 00:49:36,535
Let's see where he heads off to.

953
00:49:40,206 --> 00:49:41,907
He's on the move.

954
00:49:58,072 --> 00:50:00,232
They hit the subcontractors too?

955
00:50:00,232 --> 00:50:01,992
What's gotten into MD Kwon?

956
00:50:01,992 --> 00:50:03,313
What's Director Song saying?

957
00:50:03,313 --> 00:50:05,739
His secretary said he rushed out earlier,

958
00:50:05,739 --> 00:50:07,900
and he hasn't picked up since.

959
00:50:07,900 --> 00:50:11,570
Sounds like he's out wrangling the vendors.

960
00:50:11,570 --> 00:50:14,553
Tell MD Kwon to stop blowing this up.

961
00:50:14,553 --> 00:50:16,812
Why act up at such a critical time?

962
00:50:16,812 --> 00:50:19,110
Yes, sir.

963
00:50:23,749 --> 00:50:25,517
Book me a massage somewhere.

964
00:50:25,517 --> 00:50:27,867
The kind chairmen go for.

965
00:50:27,867 --> 00:50:28,987
A painless one.

966
00:50:28,987 --> 00:50:30,422
Right away, sir.

967
00:50:30,422 --> 00:50:32,260
I can't handle pain.

968
00:50:38,572 --> 00:50:40,465
Where are we right now?

969
00:50:57,972 --> 00:50:59,718
You know this place?

970
00:50:59,718 --> 00:51:01,289
I know it all too well.

971
00:51:01,289 --> 00:51:03,277
This is Jae Seong's in-laws' place,

972
00:51:04,046 --> 00:51:06,372
Chairman Na Byeong Mo of Taeha Group.

973
00:51:06,372 --> 00:51:08,788
Director Song was working for Chairman Na?

974
00:51:08,788 --> 00:51:10,932
He probably planted him there from day one.

975
00:51:10,932 --> 00:51:12,305
He waited for the moment

976
00:51:12,305 --> 00:51:15,327
Director Song could get full grip
on the slush fund.

977
00:51:15,327 --> 00:51:18,187
That slippery old fox.

978
00:51:18,187 --> 00:51:22,274
But Chairman Na wants his son-in-law
to take Choiseong, why this?

979
00:51:22,274 --> 00:51:24,509
He wants leverage on Kang Jae Seong.

980
00:51:24,509 --> 00:51:28,049
Manipulate the dumb son-in-law
and swallow Choiseong. That's the play.

981
00:51:30,479 --> 00:51:32,459
This works out.

982
00:51:32,459 --> 00:51:35,187
We grab Director Song, squeeze the slush fund,

983
00:51:35,187 --> 00:51:37,256
expose the hit-and-run,
and make him pay for it,

984
00:51:37,256 --> 00:51:39,936
then Taeha pulls out of Choiseong on their own,

985
00:51:39,936 --> 00:51:42,063
and everything works out.

986
00:51:42,063 --> 00:51:43,528
No.

987
00:51:45,239 --> 00:51:47,739
We're taking the slush fund.

988
00:51:47,739 --> 00:51:49,079
What?

989
00:51:49,079 --> 00:51:51,605
If we expose it right now,

990
00:51:51,605 --> 00:51:53,438
who ends up as chairman?

991
00:51:54,172 --> 00:51:56,036
Jae Gyeong did her share of stealing too.

992
00:51:56,036 --> 00:51:58,110
The hit-and-run, obviously.

993
00:51:58,110 --> 00:52:00,949
<i>She even tried to kill me.</i>

994
00:52:03,770 --> 00:52:06,117
I'll throw both of them out.

995
00:52:08,006 --> 00:52:10,959
His slush fund is the seed money for that.

996
00:52:10,959 --> 00:52:13,444
That three hundred billion
at Choiseong Trading,

997
00:52:13,444 --> 00:52:15,293
we're going to siphon it off.

998
00:52:19,273 --> 00:52:21,524
Stay right on his tail.

999
00:52:21,524 --> 00:52:24,136
He's wrapping this up today, I'm sure of it.

1000
00:52:24,136 --> 00:52:26,441
Go!

1001
00:52:38,350 --> 00:52:40,028
Still no word from Director Song?

1002
00:52:40,028 --> 00:52:41,853
I checked with Yujin's CEO,

1003
00:52:41,853 --> 00:52:43,572
and Director Song said he'd handle it himself,

1004
00:52:43,572 --> 00:52:45,557
never even met with them.

1005
00:52:47,173 --> 00:52:49,061
He better not be playing games with me.

1006
00:52:49,061 --> 00:52:50,696
What? Playing games?

1007
00:52:50,696 --> 00:52:52,106
He said let's switch accounts,

1008
00:52:52,106 --> 00:52:54,145
so I trusted him with everything,

1009
00:52:54,145 --> 00:52:55,712
three hundred billion of mine.

1010
00:52:55,712 --> 00:52:57,168
What?

1011
00:52:59,438 --> 00:53:01,973
That son of a bitch!

1012
00:53:03,972 --> 00:53:05,338
Sir,

1013
00:53:05,338 --> 00:53:07,546
it looks like Director Song
moved his family out too,

1014
00:53:07,546 --> 00:53:09,351
and the house is already on the market.

1015
00:53:09,351 --> 00:53:11,350
Find Song Nam Hoon,

1016
00:53:11,350 --> 00:53:13,051
right now!

1017
00:53:27,072 --> 00:53:30,202
Director Song just vanished?

1018
00:53:30,202 --> 00:53:31,247
Yes,

1019
00:53:31,247 --> 00:53:33,838
Secretary Nam has men out hunting for him.

1020
00:53:34,509 --> 00:53:37,757
There's no way he stabbed Jae Seong alone.

1021
00:53:39,139 --> 00:53:41,104
Dig deeper into this.

1022
00:53:41,104 --> 00:53:43,318
Check what Taeha Group is up to.

1023
00:53:43,318 --> 00:53:44,806
Yes, ma'am.

1024
00:53:45,584 --> 00:53:48,472
What's the big project
Director Song runs at Trading?

1025
00:53:48,472 --> 00:53:50,989
It's the Yuncheon Port project.

1026
00:53:50,989 --> 00:53:53,472
<i>The stock rose thanks to Choiseong Trading</i>

1027
00:53:53,472 --> 00:53:57,996
<i>making news with the Yuncheon SOC project.</i>

1028
00:53:57,996 --> 00:54:00,499
Set up an exec meeting in an hour.

1029
00:54:00,499 --> 00:54:02,200
Have them come ready with ideas

1030
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:04,339
on how Chemicals can grab it.

1031
00:54:04,339 --> 00:54:05,737
Got it.

1032
00:54:18,854 --> 00:54:20,585
There she is.

1033
00:54:29,572 --> 00:54:30,654
What's going on, honey?

1034
00:54:30,654 --> 00:54:32,572
Take this.

1035
00:54:32,572 --> 00:54:33,640
It's all in dollars.

1036
00:54:33,640 --> 00:54:35,033
Head straight to Incheon Port.

1037
00:54:35,033 --> 00:54:36,672
I sent the ferry details to your phone,

1038
00:54:36,672 --> 00:54:39,237
- so take the kids and lay low in China first.
- What about you?

1039
00:54:39,237 --> 00:54:41,273
I'll catch up with you soon.

1040
00:54:41,273 --> 00:54:42,639
There's no time. Move, now.

1041
00:54:42,639 --> 00:54:44,242
Okay.

1042
00:54:51,383 --> 00:54:52,644
[President Kang Jae Seong]

1043
00:54:54,319 --> 00:54:55,394
[President Kang Jae Seong]

1044
00:55:03,577 --> 00:55:05,267
What?

1045
00:55:05,267 --> 00:55:07,866
What is that?

1046
00:55:15,972 --> 00:55:17,609
What the...

1047
00:56:00,285 --> 00:56:02,824
You laundered it through crypto?

1048
00:56:04,472 --> 00:56:06,258
Yes, Chairman.

1049
00:56:06,258 --> 00:56:10,162
President Kang's full 300 billion slush fund

1050
00:56:10,162 --> 00:56:13,305
is sitting inside this crypto wallet app.

1051
00:56:13,305 --> 00:56:15,605
And right here,

1052
00:56:15,605 --> 00:56:17,569
you've got the ID and password.

1053
00:56:18,772 --> 00:56:20,839
Since it's crypto-based money,

1054
00:56:20,839 --> 00:56:22,644
it can't be traced at all.

1055
00:56:22,644 --> 00:56:24,083
You've got nothing to worry about.

1056
00:56:24,083 --> 00:56:26,982
The world's changing so fast.

1057
00:56:26,982 --> 00:56:29,281
How's an old man like me supposed to keep up?

1058
00:56:29,281 --> 00:56:31,015
Don't you think?

1059
00:56:32,220 --> 00:56:34,605
Sending my own man into someone else's house,

1060
00:56:34,605 --> 00:56:37,201
I haven't had a peaceful day since.

1061
00:56:37,201 --> 00:56:39,292
You know that, right?

1062
00:56:39,292 --> 00:56:42,030
Take a year off and come back rested.

1063
00:56:42,030 --> 00:56:46,064
I'll keep the Taeha Chemicals
president seat open for you.

1064
00:56:46,064 --> 00:56:48,145
Thank you, sir.

1065
00:56:48,145 --> 00:56:49,834
Have a piece.

1066
00:56:53,138 --> 00:56:56,273
Once you hit the tropics,

1067
00:56:56,273 --> 00:56:58,509
you'll be missing this flavor.

1068
00:57:43,264 --> 00:57:46,290
Now I can finally eat in peace.

1069
00:58:19,190 --> 00:58:20,725
Did you have any clue

1070
00:58:20,725 --> 00:58:23,331
Chairman Na was capable of this?

1071
00:58:23,331 --> 00:58:25,539
I didn't think he'd go this far.

1072
00:58:25,539 --> 00:58:27,965
Though that guy's the one
taking it the hardest.

1073
00:58:43,839 --> 00:58:46,384
<i>What the hell?</i>

1074
00:58:50,072 --> 00:58:52,156
<i>What the...</i>

1075
00:59:14,187 --> 00:59:17,087
<i>Working hard to deliver
Kang Jae Seong's slush money, huh?</i>

1076
00:59:17,087 --> 00:59:20,518
<i>Chairman Na's loyal little hound,
jumping at his every word.</i>

1077
00:59:22,106 --> 00:59:24,422
<i>You're that intern?</i>

1078
00:59:24,422 --> 00:59:27,505
<i>Kang Jae Seong's probably
hunting you down right now.</i>

1079
00:59:27,505 --> 00:59:30,428
<i>And Chairman Na is too sharp
to let you walk after that.</i>

1080
00:59:30,428 --> 00:59:33,287
<i>Where'd you pick up
this garbage you're spewing?</i>

1081
00:59:33,287 --> 00:59:35,367
<i>That's not a name
a punk like you gets to throw around.</i>

1082
00:59:35,367 --> 00:59:36,801
<i>Get lost.</i>

1083
00:59:38,505 --> 00:59:40,938
<i>If you want to live,
listen close to what I say.</i>

1084
00:59:42,352 --> 00:59:44,505
<i>When you hand the slush fund to Chairman Na,</i>

1085
00:59:44,505 --> 00:59:47,152
<i>hold back the QR access code.</i>

1086
00:59:47,879 --> 00:59:49,113
<i>What kind of nonsense is that?</i>

1087
00:59:49,113 --> 00:59:52,984
<i>Hand over all 300 billion and die, or else...</i>

1088
00:59:53,972 --> 00:59:56,358
<i>What's there to lose?</i>

1089
00:59:56,358 --> 00:59:58,589
<i>Try putting your trust in me for once.</i>

1090
01:00:28,052 --> 01:00:29,487
<i>Damn it.</i>

1091
01:00:43,505 --> 01:00:45,970
Your life belongs to me now.

1092
01:00:46,871 --> 01:00:48,739
And that debt,

1093
01:00:48,739 --> 01:00:51,108
you'll pay it back
with Jae Seong's slush money.

1094
01:00:53,672 --> 01:00:55,146
What's wrong?

1095
01:00:55,847 --> 01:00:58,424
Now that you're alive, getting greedy?

1096
01:00:58,424 --> 01:01:00,718
Tempted to pocket all 300 billion yourself?

1097
01:01:01,327 --> 01:01:02,887
Whether it's Chairman Na or Jae Seong,

1098
01:01:02,887 --> 01:01:05,557
there isn't a soul out there
who'd welcome you back.

1099
01:01:05,557 --> 01:01:07,358
No, that's not it.

1100
01:01:07,358 --> 01:01:10,305
I'll hand it over.

1101
01:01:10,305 --> 01:01:13,397
Take all of it.

1102
01:01:16,006 --> 01:01:19,003
That's enough to keep your family fed for life.

1103
01:01:26,338 --> 01:01:28,483
Spend the rest of your days in hiding.

1104
01:01:28,483 --> 01:01:30,718
Where no one can ever find you.

1105
01:01:52,404 --> 01:01:54,839
So, do you trust me now?

1106
01:01:54,839 --> 01:01:56,834
This is terrifying.

1107
01:01:56,834 --> 01:01:59,543
I saw it with my own eyes
and still can't process it.

1108
01:02:00,478 --> 01:02:02,780
How is any of this even real?

1109
01:02:02,780 --> 01:02:05,585
Come on, this is only the beginning.

1110
01:02:05,585 --> 01:02:07,989
I should keep my promise to your father.

1111
01:02:07,989 --> 01:02:10,492
Let's take Choiseong back

1112
01:02:10,492 --> 01:02:11,823
from Jae Gyeong and Jae Seong,

1113
01:02:11,823 --> 01:02:13,457
you and me, together.

1114
01:02:50,672 --> 01:02:52,507
<i>So, are we officially on the same side now?</i>

1115
01:02:52,507 --> 01:02:53,965
<i>We use Jae Gyeong to pull every last fang</i>

1116
01:02:53,965 --> 01:02:55,333
<i>right out of Jae Seong's mouth.</i>

1117
01:02:55,333 --> 01:02:56,548
<i>Why don't you take a gamble on me?</i>

1118
01:02:56,548 --> 01:02:59,207
<i>If it flops, you can cut me loose then.</i>

1119
01:02:59,207 --> 01:03:01,238
<i>Let's share a drink, just you and me.</i>

1120
01:03:01,972 --> 01:03:03,128
<i>Who is that guy?</i>

1121
01:03:03,128 --> 01:03:04,492
<i>Hey, aren't you a soccer player?</i>

1122
01:03:04,492 --> 01:03:07,679
<i>The truth is, I'm Chairman Kang's youngest son.</i>

1123
01:03:07,679 --> 01:03:08,688
<i>I hit the big time.</i>

1124
01:03:08,688 --> 01:03:10,248
<i>My lips are sealed tight.</i>

1125
01:03:10,248 --> 01:03:11,449
<i>It'll be a whole lot easier.</i>

1126
01:03:11,449 --> 01:03:12,788
<i>We've already won this thing.</i>

1127
01:03:12,788 --> 01:03:14,588
<i>That bastard deserves to be ground into dust.</i>

1128
01:03:14,588 --> 01:03:16,088
<i>But you really think
Chairman Na will sit still?</i>

1129
01:03:16,088 --> 01:03:17,408
<i>- Want me to lend a hand?
- Thank you.</i>

1130
01:03:17,408 --> 01:03:20,128
<i>Where the hell is this coming from
out of nowhere?</i>

1131
01:03:20,128 --> 01:03:23,798
<i>Your time with Choiseong ends right here.
We're done.</i>

1132
01:03:23,798 --> 01:03:25,596
<i>Yeah, that's not happening.</i>

